<TITLE> Damage figures of govt agencies widely vary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 20 (bdnews24.com)  Government agencies were posting widely varying death toll and damage estimates in the aftermath of cyclone Sidr. The food and disaster management ministry put the death counts at 2,817 at 9am Tuesday. It counted 6,611 injured, 2,062 missing and 10, 54, 885 families or 40,83,568 people displaced by the cyclone at the same time Tuesday. The home ministry control room reported the death toll to be 2,752 at 9am Tuesday. In sharp contrast, the army's disaster management wing said the death toll stood at 3,447 at 11am Tuesday, with 3,322 injured, 1,063 missing, 9,11,045 families or 32,72,562 people displaced by the disaster. The chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim had told reporters that the food and disaster management ministry would provide the focal point for the government's efforts. The duty officer at the home ministry control room, senior assistant secretary Babar Ali Mir, told bdnews24.com that their figures were collected from the district's control room. They had been provided only with death estimates, he said. Efforts to obtain other information had so far been unsuccessful, he added. bdnews24.com
